author: The Emporia Gazette
title: Area volleyball capsules
text:
Area volleyball capsules The Emporia Gazette emporiagazette.com | 0 comments 
Chase County’s volleyball team swept West Franklin in a two-match dual Tuesday, with both victories requiring three sets. 
The Bulldogs opened with a 25-13 win in the first set, but dropped the next 15-25 to force a third. Chase County rebounded with a 25-20 win to end the match. 
Chase County’s second match also ended with a win, but it required more of a comeback after the Bulldogs lost the first set 25-27. The Bulldogs turned the table with a 27-25 win in the second set before finishing off West Franklin with a 25-23 victory to improve to 16-11 on the season. 
Bailee Swift and Molly Soyez led Chase County in the front row, with 13 and 10 kills, respectively. Paige Burkhart blocked four total attacks, while Soyez (30) and Kassady Griffin (23) led the team in digs. 
Council Grove sweeps Lyndon 
Council Grove topped another Flint Hills League opponent in Lyndon Tuesday, responding from a 23-25 loss with consecutive 25-9 wins in the first match. 
The Braves’ momentum carried over into the second match, which saw them win in two sets (25-18, 25-15) to improve to 19-4 on the season and a perfect 10-0 in league play. 
Maddy Tischhauser and Adree Honas both collected 10 kills in the first match against the Tigers, with Erica Auchard adding seven. Milo Butler proved to be a valuable weapon on serves, recording nine aces in 28 attempts to go with 25 assists and 14 digs. 
Mattea Tompkins posted a team-high seven kills in the second match, with Auchard’s five ranking second. 
NHHS splits with Osage City 
Northern Heights split its two-match dual against Osage City Tuesday. 
The Wildcats lost the first match 22-25, 16-25, but bounced back with a sweep of their own that included wins of 25-20, 25-19. 
Jordan Wooderson led NHHS with nine kills. She also collected 11 digs and six aces. Natalie Leffler added seven kills and 11 digs while Breanna Brecheisen posted a double-double with 13 assists and 10 digs to go with five aces. Tristan Guzman led the Wildcats with 13 digs.
